abstract: The Dow, S.& P. and Nasdaq ended the week more than 2 percent higher.
snippet: The Dow, S.& P. and Nasdaq ended the week more than 2 percent higher.
lead_paragraph: A lot of numbers are shouted out on the floor of the New York Stock Exchange during a typical trading day, and on Friday, soccer scores were among them.

headline.main: One Eye on World Cup, Wall Street Quietly Rises
